00:01:02,752 --> 00:01:04,435
(Simple Explanations).

16
00:01:04,435 --> 00:01:08,798
Before we dive into code, let's understand what these acronyms actually mean.

17
00:01:08,798 --> 00:01:10,877
Augmented Reality (AR).

18
00:01:10,877 --> 00:01:14,038
Digital content overlaid on the real world.

19
00:01:14,038 --> 00:01:19,014
Think Pokémon GO, Instagram filters, or IKEA's furniture placement app.

20
00:01:19,014 --> 00:01:23,076
You still see the real world - just with digital elements added on top.

21
00:01:23,076 --> 00:01:25,108
Virtual Reality (VR).

22
00:01:25,108 --> 00:01:28,930
Completely digital environment that replaces the real world.

23
00:01:28,930 --> 00:01:32,920
Put on a VR headset, and you're transported somewhere else entirely.

24
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:36,117
You see only the virtual world - full immersion.

25
00:01:36,117 --> 00:01:37,980
Mixed Reality (MR).

26
00:01:37,980 --> 00:01:40,865
Digital objects that interact with the real world.

27
00:01:40,865 --> 00:01:43,593
A virtual ball bouncing off your real table.

28
00:01:43,593 --> 00:01:46,538
A digital character sitting on your actual couch.

29
00:01:46,538 --> 00:01:50,492
Real and digital worlds interact - most advanced form.

30
00:01:50,492 --> 00:01:52,716
Extended Reality (XR).

31
00:01:52,716 --> 00:02:02,379
The umbrella term covering AR, VR, and MR. When people say "XR development," they mean building for any or all of these platforms.

